<b>Symptoms</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The signs of Cerebral Palsy become visible during infancy or early school years of a child. It can lead to abnormal bone development and posture of the body, creating floppiness or rigidity of the limbs. Less control over facial muscles, speech impairment and difficulties in swallowing and feeding are some of the symptoms seen in such cases. It is treatable to an extent but there is no cure.Â </span>

