<span style="font-weight: 400;">Kids with CP lack proper coordination to feed themselves, chew and sometimes even swallow the food without choking.Â  Mealtimes can be made less challenging with proper techniques. A trained nutritionist can provide the proper guidance to make sure the child with CP receives nutrients and supplements based on their lifestyle activities. Special care needs to be taken especially in the case of calcium and Vit. D deficiencies.</span>

